Personal life
Hester is in a relationship with Tamara James, a women's basketball player he met at the University of Miami. James currently plays professionally for the Washington Mystics. In an interview with the Black Sports Network in 2005, Hester revealed that he was engaged to James, but the couple had not yet set a date for their marriage ceremony.;Black Sports Network, [http://www.blacksportsnetwork.com/articles/qa/hester_090305.asp College Football: Devin] Retrieved on November 17, 2006; A later article by the ''Chicago Tribune'' confirmed that he had proposed to James on June 6, 2005 at a Miami Heat basketball game.; Chicago Tribune,[http://www.chicagotribune.com/sports/cs-060917haugh,1,5287462.column?coll=chi-sportstop-hed Pilot episode is prime-time] Retrieved on December 18, 2006 ; Hester’s family resides in Florida and was struck by Hurricane Wilma in 2005. Hester has assisted his family financially in helping them rebuild their home.;Scout.com, [http://bears.scout.com/2/591150.html Devin Hester Rookie Diary: Entry 1] Retrieved on November 17, 2006; His brother Lenorris Jr., resides with Hester during the regular season in their Chicago area home. Being raised in a Christian household, Hester brings a Bible to every game he plays.;Sun Sentinel, [http://web.archive.org/web/20070119013722/http://www.sun-sentinel.com/sports/football/pro/dolphins/sfl-sphester16jan16,0,1250224.story?coll=sfla-dolphins-front Devin Hester's kick returns can inspire cheers or cringing] Retrieved on January 16, 2007;

Hester’s successful rookie year drew him much publicity and popularity. Ever since his record-breaking performance against the Rams, Hester has been offered marketing opportunities from Nike Inc.|Nike, soft drink, and cell phone companies.;ChicagoBears.com, [http://www.chicagobears.com/multimedia/index.asp?mm_file_id=616&amp;play_clip=Y Devin Hester on success as a rookie (Video)] Retrieved on December 18,2006;
There has also been a surge in the demand for Hester’s jerseys within the Chicagoland sporting stores.;; Also, Hester was invited to throw the ceremonial opening pitch and sing ''Take Me Out to the Ball Game'' at the Chicago Cubs' 2007 home opener.;CBS SportsLine.com, [http://sportsline.com/mlb/gamecenter/recap/MLB_20070409_HOU@CHC First Wrigley outing for Piniella, Soriano ends with defeat], Retrieved on October 8, 2007.; Along with teammates Rex Grossman and Tommie Harris, Hester appeared on the February 2007 issue of ''Sports Illustrated for Kids''. His reputation has also been bolstered by EA Sports' ''Madden NFL 08'', where Hester's perfect 100 speed rating made him the fastest player in the game's history.;ESPN.com, [http://sports.espn.go.com/videogames/news/story?id=2826180 Devin Hester: Maximum Speed] Retrieved on April 6 2007; Hester also appeared in a promotional video for the game.;Youtube.com, [http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ge_Qwzdae94&amp;mode=related&amp;search= Madden 08 Draft - Devin Hester], Retrieved on June 22, 2007;

